.TH SNDFILE\-JACKPLAY 1 "May 2021" "" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
.B sndfile\-jackplay
\(em play a sound file via the JACK sound server
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sndfile\-jackplay
.RB [ OPTIONS ]
.RI < input\ sound\ file >
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B sndfile\-jackplay
plays the specified sound file via the JACK sound server.
It uses
.UR http://www.mega\-nerd.com/libsndfile/
libsndfile
.UE
to read the file.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-w ,\  \-\-wait [ =\fIport ]
Wait for input before starting playback; optionally auto-connect to
.I port
using Jack.
.TP
.BR \-a ,\  \-\-autoconnect [ =\fIport ]
Auto-connect to
.I port
using Jack.
.TP
.BR \-l ,\  \-\-loop [ =\fIcount ]
Loop the file
.I count
times
.RB ( 0
for infinite).
.TP
.BR \-h ,\  \-\-help
Print a help message and exit.
